properties.description: Road is broken up with potholes by heavy traffic on this section, especially annoying while wet.
Recently re-paved, probably the fastest and easiest way to get to dujiangyan. Average speed: 60-80kmh.
First 30-40km from Chengdu to Deyang, is all expending city and intersections with traffic lights and a bunch of traffic. Not very interesting.
Awesome road, brand new tarmac, no potholes. Great scenery and low on traffic.
Mostly an empty 8 lane tarmac road, newly constructed, no traffic.
Crazy beautiful road, twisting and turning. Awesome scenery and no traffic! Highly recommended!
Fast and boring, city to city hopping. Be careful for loony drivers and ebikes.

Known to be impassable, only bother attempting with a dirt bike or dual sport. (ask locals before you go). Motorbikes are allowed to take the expressway to avoid this, so only attempt the G road if you got the balls!
Great condition. Up to Ebian possibility of hitting SUV traffic in the weekends/holidays. After Ebian empty twisty roads and good scenery
High mountain pass, awesome scenery but be careful altitude goes up to 2900 meters and possibility of ice & snow in the colder months
